&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WARD RECEPTIONIST Hogarth Ward&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: Band 2: pro-rata to £18,005-£19,337 per annum&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: 15&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hogarth Ward is a busy and dynamic Oncology Ward admitting both emergency and elective admissions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking for an enthusiastic and motivated individual to join our receptionist team on Hogarth Ward working 15 hours per week. Your involvement in our team will help fulfil our commitment to delivering excellent quality care to our patients. Duties include greeting patients &amp; visitors when they arrive onto the ward, rebooking appointments as well as clinical note preparation and assisting the nurses with errands.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be an enthusiastic and reliable team player, able to work under pressure, have excellent customer service skills, the ability to organise and prioritise your workload accordingly and have excellent written and verbal skills; you must also have a clear understanding of confidentiality issues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be computer literate though full training will be given on NUH specific computer programmes. You will be expected to work without direct supervision after a period of training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The unit is committed to providing the highest quality of care and maintaining consistently high standards in a professional and friendly atmosphere.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NUH has a set of values and behaviours which are summarised in the job description for this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
